BA89992645B330A0564A27A0C389973A: Spawns a drivable Rocket Racing Vehicle that can be configured.

UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.On Player: A player enters the spawned vehicle
A player exits the spawned vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.On Vehicle: A vehicle is spawned or respawned.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.RequiredDe: Amount of seconds the user must hold the demolish button for in order to demolish their vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Apply OffR: Apply off-road tires to the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.SurfaceLat: Controls what surfaces the vehicle will attempt to latch onto when running into them in the air. Values range from a completely upside down surface (180 degrees) to a flat, upright surface (0 degrees).
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.SurfaceCou: Controls what surfaces the vehicle will stick to when grounded on them. Values range from a completely upside down surface (180 degrees) to a flat, upright surface (0 degrees).
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Vehicle He: Determines how much damage the vehicle can take before destruction.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Vehicle In: Determines if the Vehicle can be destroyed by damage.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Destroy wh: Determines if the Vehicle will destroy itself when stuck underwater.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.EnableResp: Determines if the Vehicle will respawn after being destroyed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.VehicleCan: Determines if the vehicle can be instantly destroyed when colliding with the world.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Enabled Du: Determines the game phases during which the device will be enabled. If set to CREATE ONLY, will only be enabled while editing your Island.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.OversteerT: Determines when the vehicle should naturally enter a drift from oversteer while continually steering in one direction. A lower value results in more slippery behavior.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.ThrustMete: Determines whether or not the Thrust Meter fully replenishes when the vehicle's tires touch a surface.
Determines whether or not the Thrust Meter will regenerate over time.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.OversteerE: Determines whether or not the vehicle is able to naturally oversteer while turning.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.AirDodgeRe: Determines whether the Air Dodge count gets reset each time the vehicle's wheels touch a surface.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Visible Du: Determines whether the device is visible during the game. This does affect its collision properties.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.WallRicoch: Determines whether the vehicle will naturally ricochet off objects when colliding with them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Only Ricoc: Determines whether the vehicle will only ricochet off of track pieces when wall ricochet is enabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Disable.De: Disable the Vehicle Spawner, stopping it from spawning any more vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Enable.Des: Enable the Vehicle Spawner, allowing it to spawn vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.ThrustMete: How fast the Thrust Meter is consumed when the Thrust button is held.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.DriftBoost: How long the player keeps their Drift Boost Speed bonus gained after a successful drift.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.TurboStart: How many tanks of Turbo a player starts with.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.AirDodgeCo: How many times the player can Air Dodge while airborne.
How much force is applied when using the jump ability.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.TurboSpeed: How much speed the player receives when using Turbo.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.DriftBoost: How much speed you gain after exiting a boost.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.TurboPassi: How quickly Turbo Tanks fill up passively (not from drifting).
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.TurboDrift: How quickly Turbo Tanks fill up while in a drift.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.BaseBrakin: How quickly the vehicle comes to a stop when holding the brake.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.BaseAccele: How quickly the vehicle gains speed while the throttle is held.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.BaseDecele: How quickly the vehicle slows down while throttle is not held.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.DriftBoost: How quickly you fill your Drift Boost Meter while drifting.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Allowed Cl: If set to All, All Classes (including players with NO CLASS) are affected. Otherwise, the chosen Class will be used to determine the Affects Class effect. ANY CLASS - Players with a Class assigned, regardless of what Class it is. NO CLASS - Players without any assigned class.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.DriftDecel: If the vehicle is above the Drift Top Speed, this affects how rapidly your vehicle will lose speed during a drift.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.DriftAccel: If the vehicle is below the Drift Top Speed, this affects how rapidly your vehicle will continue to accelerate toward that top speed during a drift.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Destroy Ve: If the vehicle that this spawner created still exists, destroy it.
ON will destroy an already spawned vehicle when this spawner is disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Only Ricoc: Only Ricochet Off Of Track Pieces
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Pop All Ti: Pop all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to pop.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Repair All: Repair all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to repair.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Repair Veh: Restore the spawned vehicle to full health.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Remove Tir: Revert to road tires on the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.GravityAer: Scales the forces of gravity while in the air.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.VehicleCol: Scales up or down the speed required to destroy the vehicle when running into a wall.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Assigns Dr: Seats the player that instigated the message as the spawned vehicle's driver.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Respawn Ve: Spawns the vehicle (Destroying the existing vehicle if it still exists).
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Activating: The Team this device belongs to.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Thruster F: The amount of force that is applied when Thrusters are active.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.ThrustMete: The amount of time it takes for the Thrust Meter to begin replenishing over time after you have released the Thrust button.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.TurboBonus: The amount of time that is added to the duration of Turbo if a player successfully activates a turbo bonus zone.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.TurboBaseD: The amount of time the Turbo Speed duration lasts.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.AirDodgeUs: The amount of time the user must wait after executing an air dodge before they can execute another.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Thruster M: The max upward speed that Thrusters can achieve while active.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.BaseMaximu: The maximum base speed that players can achieve while traveling in the air. If above this value, the vehicle will start to lose speed after a short delay.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.DriftTopSp: The maximum base speed that players can be traveling while in a drift. If above this value, the vehicle will start to lose speed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.ThrustMete: The rate at which Thrust replenishes over time while it is not being consumed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.VehicleCan: Vehicle Can be Destroyed from Collision
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.ThrustMete: What percentage of Thrust Meter the vehicle starts with.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Water Dest: When the vehicle becomes too deep in water to drive, destroy it after this delay.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Respawn Ti: When the vehicle is destroyed, respawn it after this delay. (The first vehicle spawned does not use this delay.)
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.bSelfDemol: Whether the user is able to demolish their own vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.BaseTopSpe: Without any boost or turbo modifiers, how fast this vehicle can go given the time to get there.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_DelMarVehicleSpawner_C.Respawn Ve: YES will spawn a vehicle when the device is enabled. ONLY IF NEEDED will not reset an existing vehicle.
